DDD ( Display Disc Details ) is a simple utility to list the contents of a
disc - floppy or RAM only I'm afraid, I don't have a hard disk  to try it on.
It follows directories to their contents, using indentation to show the
relationships between them. Folders are indicated by a * prefix (plus of
course they dont have a size or date-last-written).
Default output is to the screen. To direct the output to printer, enter
          >>prt:
as a parameter.
As well as disk contents it shows volume name (if any) and space used & free.

The prog is written in Mark Johnsons shareware C, widely available from PD
libraries, both to teach myself C, to try out the compiler, and because I 
wanted the utility to use. I hope you find it useful.

Terry Billany 25/6/88
